<section id="architecture">
    <h2>1. Computer Architecture</h2>
    <p>A computer system follows the Von Neumann architecture consisting of CPU, memory, I/O devices, and system buses.</p>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=db666918bf4b320b98da3710bef644e4036a30120d64750f647b0372437ee3e1JmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=computer+architecture&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvQ29tcHV0ZXJfYXJjaGl0ZWN0dXJl">Click to know more about architecture</a>
    <h3>Central Processing Unit (CPU)</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>ALU:</b> Performs arithmetic and logical operations</li>
        <li><b>Control Unit:</b> Directs operations and instruction execution</li>
        <li><b>Registers:</b> High-speed storage inside CPU</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section id="memory">
    <h2>2. Memory Hierarchy</h2>
    <p>Memory is arranged based on speed, cost, and capacity.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Registers</li>
        <li>Cache Memory</li>
        <li>Main Memory (RAM)</li>
        <li>Secondary Storage</li>
        <li>Tertiary Storage</li>
        <li>Virtual Memory</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="#https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=4b73716092b88acca71f24f5dedbc9b4c4c02e1ab919b9fa7df99f5a52700bfeJmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=memory+hierarchy&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvTWVtb3J5X2hpZXJhcmNoeQ">Click to know more about memory Hierarchy</a>
</section>

<section id="registers">
    <h2>3. Registers</h2>
    <p>Registers are small, fast storage locations inside the CPU.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Accumulator (AC)</li>
        <li>Program Counter (PC)</li>
        <li>Instruction Register (IR)</li>
        <li>Memory Address Register (MAR)</li>
        <li>Memory Data Register (MDR)</li>
        <li>Status Register</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=a68c24b7332df2bc797a95f3fc53df56673036d8f974f267123ab36ccf58d537JmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=registers+in+cpu&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlaW90YWNhZGVteS5jby9ibG9nL3JlZ2lzdGVycy1pbi1jcHUv">More about Registers</a>
</section>

<section id="cache">
    <h2>4. Cache Memory</h2>
    <p>Cache stores frequently accessed data to speed up CPU processing.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>L1 Cache – Fastest</li>
        <li>L2 Cache – Moderate</li>
        <li>L3 Cache – Shared among cores</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=61937d54c0be9f5c77d2d955847e1b4e4ecada1d1ccaa87720c3702196c4f985JmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=cache+memory&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ2Vla3Nmb3JnZWVrcy5vcmcvY29tcHV0ZXItc2NpZW5jZS1mdW5kYW1lbnRhbHMvY2FjaGUtbWVtb3J5Lw">More about Cache</a>
</section>

<section id="ram">
    <h2>5. RAM</h2>
    <p>RAM is volatile memory used as the working space of the computer.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>DRAM</li>
        <li>SRAM</li>
        <li>DDR1 – DDR5</li>
    </ul>
     <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=35ec484f367a247b7545377efcad7404bd8a176b950003a2c04207550832b8faJmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=ram&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvUmFuZG9tLWFjY2Vzc19tZW1vcnk">More about RAM</a>
</section>

<section id="virtual">
    <h2>6. Virtual Memory</h2>
    <p>Virtual memory uses storage space as an extension of RAM.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Paging</li>
        <li>Swap Space</li>
        <li>MMU</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=cebe41e3c554323813b773bbbd8845d646c2763296a2b7427128dd59264796faJmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=virtual+memory&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ2Vla3Nmb3JnZWVrcy5vcmcvb3BlcmF0aW5nLXN5c3RlbXMvdmlydHVhbC1tZW1vcnktaW4tb3BlcmF0aW5nLXN5c3RlbS8">More about Virtual Memory</a>
</section>

<section id="motherboard">
    <h2>7. Motherboard</h2>
    <p>The motherboard connects all computer components.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>CPU Socket</li>
        <li>RAM Slots</li>
        <li>Chipset</li>
        <li>Expansion Slots</li>
        <li>BIOS/UEFI</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=90913162d145f0404aa567fe8ef93bcdbdc8c86f3cf4ffd54911dbf1cadf8f9fJmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=motherboard&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvTW90aGVyYm9hcmQ">More about Motherboard</a>
</section>

<section id="io">
    <h2>8. Input & Output Devices</h2>
    <h3>Input Devices</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Keyboard</li>
        <li>Mouse</li>
        <li>Scanner</li>
        <li>Microphone</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Output Devices</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Monitor</li>
        <li>Printer</li>
        <li>Speakers</li>
        <li>Projector</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=3d33e1f7f9b5b7f96cf74a851e1ff8f3c8b6c9e113b58a3b8c26470a4f1e873eJmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=input+and+output+devices&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ2Vla3Nmb3JnZWVrcy5vcmcvY29tcHV0ZXItc2NpZW5jZS1mdW5kYW1lbnRhbHMvaW5wdXQtYW5kLW91dHB1dC1kZXZpY2VzLw">More about I/O Devices</a>
</section>

<section id="buses">
    <h2>9. Buses</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Data Bus</li>
        <li>Address Bus</li>
        <li>Control Bus</li>
        <li>PCIe, USB, SATA</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=19734e3a513945d6795cb57038a20ef86947b6df21bbd4ad7cc14d0b4f491887JmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=buses+in+computer+architecture&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvQnVzXyhjb21wdXRpbmcp">More about Buses</a>
</section>

<section id="firmware">
    <h2>10. Firmware</h2>
    <p>Firmware is permanent software stored in hardware.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>BIOS/UEFI</li>
        <li>Embedded Systems</li>
        <li>Router Firmware</li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=643cce3efdcfca9df54283d0a1ed4e07f1e7cd4cd47d6e022dcab58667515c20JmltdHM9MTc2OTgxNzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=357f2228-01fc-629c-0885-3607005163be&psq=firmware&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvRmlybXdhcmU">More about Firmware</a>
</section>

